- Tournament group support: Director Portal can view/update per-group starting holes, server endpoints exist (`GET/PUT /group-starting-holes`), storage persists `groupStartingHoles`, and tournament game start reads group-assigned hole.
- UI progress updates: Game screen now shows hole plus played-count progress (`Hole X` + `Y/18 played`).
- Leaderboards: live leaderboard surfaces holes completed in both director views and in-game tournament leaderboard; live-standings note appears when groups are on different holes.

Comments (non-blocking):
1) Director leaderboard wording/format is slightly inconsistent across views (some places show `X/18`, one full leaderboard row shows `X holes`). Functionally acceptable, but inconsistent with the explicit `X/18` requirement phrasing.
2) Diff includes substantial unrelated changes (sponsor flow, broader UI behavior changes). Not a blocker for this task, but increases regression surface and makes verification harder.

Security: none observed (no serious authz/injection/secret-handling regressions specific to this task).

Next actions:
1) Normalize leaderboard hole-progress display to `X/18` in all director leaderboard variants for consistency.
2) If possible, split unrelated sponsor/UI changes into separate PR/task to reduce deployment risk and simplify rollback/testing.
